{"id":683035,"date":"2023-12-30T16:08:50","date_gmt":"2023-12-30T10:38:50","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/?p=683035"},"modified":"2024-10-21T17:27:09","modified_gmt":"2024-10-21T11:57:09","slug":"ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences","title":{"rendered":"BA vs BA Honors: Key differences\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Bachelor of Arts (BA) and Bachelor of Arts Honors (BA Hons) may seem like two peas in a pod, claiming to be the best undergraduate courses for students after 10+2. Although both sound similar in name, they have their unique flavors.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Talking about the fundamental <strong>d<\/strong>ifferences between BA and BA Honors the first and foremost is specialization. While an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/pros-and-cons-of-online-ba-for-working-professionals\">online BA course from Sikkim Manipal University<\/a> means studying at least 5 subjects, on the other hand, a BA Hons means specializing in one subject for 3 years. It is as if a BA course is like serving a dish with other 4 dishes, while a BA Honors is like serving a Biryani as the main dish.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/how-to-choose-the-right-online-ba-program\">Choosing between BA and BA Honors programs<\/a> can be challenging for many, so we thought of simplifying the choice by discussing both courses in detail in this post. So, join us to understand the key distinctions in BA and BA Honors degrees in terms of objective, eligibility, curriculum, and career prospects.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-what-is-ba\"><strong>What is BA?\u00a0<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A Bachelor of Arts (BA) degree program is the most popular UG course offered by almost all universities and colleges. It is a course that aims to allow students to explore various subjects before they proceed to a particular specialization. The main skills imparted to an online BA student from universities like Sikkim Manipal University through the Online Manipal platform are communication, critical thinking, research, and analysis skills. A BA course can be like a stepping stone that prepares students to dig deeper for diverse career paths at the postgraduate level.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-what-is-ba-honors\"><strong>What is BA Honors?<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Before throwing light on the advantages of pursuing BA Honors over a simple BA program, it is crucial to know what is BA Honors. A Bachelor of Arts Honors or a BA Hons is a 3-year undergraduate specialized degree course offered in various subjects to help individuals grab skills specific to a particular field. A BA Hons course is like an academic red carpet that invites students to step beyond the spectrum of general knowledge and attain specialized expertise in subjects like English, Political Science, and Sociology.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-eligibility-criteria-ba-vs-ba-honors\"><strong>Eligibility criteria: BA vs BA Honors\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>No matter, whether you <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/regular-vs-distance-vs-online-ba#:~:text=Pursuing%20an%20online%20BA%20degree,and%20knowledge%20for%20career%20advancement.\"><strong>choose to pursue an online BA course<\/strong> <\/a>or a BA Honors degree program, the eligibility criteria may vary from institution to institution. So, it is better to check and verify the exact eligibility requirements of the university or college you want to apply for your preferred BA or BA Hons UG course.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The standard eligibility criteria for BA and BA Honors degree programs are as follows:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>BA Course Eligibility\u00a0<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>BA Honors Course Eligibility<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Completion of 10+2 from a recognized board in either Science, Arts, or Commerce stream<\/td><td>Completion of 10+2 from a recognized board with a minimum of 50% marks<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Pass the CUET entrance exam<\/td><td>Minimum age to apply: 17 years<br>Maximum age to apply: 25 years<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-ba-course-curriculum\"><strong>BA course curriculum<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether one chooses to pursue an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/bachelor-of-arts-english\">online BA in English<\/a>, Sociology, Political Science, or any other subject, the course curriculum is designed to equip an individual with a versatile set of skills that can be applied in various professional fields. The entire BA course is split into 6 semesters that are covered in 3 years. Giving students the best choice to grasp skills in three popular subjects, English, Sociology, and Political Science, Sikkim Manipal University has launched a combination online BA course that covers all three in one program.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-ba-honors-course-curriculum\"><strong>BA Honors course curriculum\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Bachelor of Arts Honors (BA Hons) is a well-planned course that aims to inculcate an individual&#8217;s critical thinking, creativity, and clear communication skills. Those interested in pursuing a BA Honors through the Online Manipal platform can enroll at Manipal Academy of Higher Education (MAHE) in a variety of subjects like English, Sociology, Philosophy, History, German, French, and Spanish.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The course curriculum of a Bachelor of Arts Honors <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/benefits-of-online-programs-from-mahe\">(BA) Honors course at MAHE<\/a> focuses on offering fundamental concepts. However, at the end of the first semester, students can decide between three learning paths to continue studying. These are what they call Majors, Minors, and Double Majors. For this, they can opt for any of the following three options:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Explorer<\/strong><\/td><td>1 Major + 1 Minor<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Innovator<\/strong><\/td><td>1 Major + 2 Minors<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Consolidator<\/strong><\/td><td>2 Majors<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The table below shows the year-wise program structure of a BA Honors from Manipal Academy of Higher Education (MAHE):<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Year<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Semester and Program Structure<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Year 1<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Semester 1 &amp; 2:\u00a0<\/strong>Foundation courses, Extra Disciplinary Competencies<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Year 2<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Semester 3 &amp; 4:<\/strong>Major &amp; Minor Courses, Extra Disciplinary Competencies<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Year 3<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Semester 5 &amp; 6:<\/strong>Major &amp; Minor Courses, Extra Disciplinary Competencies<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Year 4<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Semester 7 &amp; 8:<\/strong>Literature Review, Research Proposal, Thesis<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/manipal.edu\/mcph\/program-list\/ba-humanities2.html\"><em>https:\/\/manipal.edu\/mcph\/program-list\/ba-humanities2.html<\/em><\/a><em>&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-career-opportunities-after-ba\"><strong>Career opportunities after BA\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A host of bright career opportunities can come your way once you get a UGC-entitled online BA degree from a top-class university like Sikkim Manipal University (SMU) through the Online Manipal platform. The knowledge and skills one grasps during this popular humanities UG course enable course graduates to fit into several exciting job roles ranging from a digital marketing manager to a human resource manager, from an academician to a content writer, and a public relations manager.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The table below highlights the<strong> <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/top-government-jobs-for-ba-graduates\"><strong>top 5 job opportunities for online BA graduates<\/strong><\/a>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Job Role<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Job Description<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Approximate Salary<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Content Writer<\/strong><\/td><td>Creating engaging content for various online and offline platforms<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/content-specialist-salary-SRCH_KO0,18.htm#:~:text=Content%20Specialist%20Salaries%20in%20India&amp;text=The%20average%20salary%20for%20Content,45%2C309%20%2D%20%E2%82%B91%2C17%2C196.\">INR 6,70,995 per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Public Relations Manager<\/strong><\/td><td>Monitoring media releases and other communications to shape a positive image of a company<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/pr-manager-salary-SRCH_KO0,10.htm\">INR 9.83 lakh per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Digital Marketing Manager<\/strong><\/td><td>Planning content strategies to boost the digital presence of a company<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/digital-marketing-salary-SRCH_KO0,17.htm\">INR 7,50,000 per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Academician<\/strong><\/td><td>Imparting knowledge and skills to interested students in a specific field<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/professor-salary#:~:text=Average%20starting%20Salary%20for%20Professor,%E2%82%B92.5L%20per%20month).\">INR 14.5 lakh per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Human Resource Manager<\/strong><\/td><td>Ensuring good relations between employees and employers and hiring the best talent for the company<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/hr-manager-salary\">INR 10 lakh &#8211; INR 12 lakh per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-career-opportunities-after-ba-honors\"><strong>Career opportunities after BA Honors\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A Bachelor of Arts Honors course, when pursued from a reputed university, can kickstart a bright career. Elaborately speaking, career options for a BA Honors graduate are not limited to jobs in the fields of content writing, human resource management, event management, or teaching; one can also get success in starting and handling a business.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The table below highlights the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/high-paying-jobs-after-online-ba\"><strong>top 5 career prospects open for BA Honors graduates<\/strong><\/a>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Job Role<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Job Description<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Approximate Salary<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Teacher\/ Professor<\/strong><\/td><td>Motivating, inspiring, and educating learners with the right skills and knowledge<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.salaryexplorer.com\/average-salary-wage-comparison-india-professor-sociology-c100j742\">INR 5,60,000 per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Content Writer<\/strong><\/td><td>Writing grammatically correct and interesting content for magazines, books, blogs, or websites<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/content-specialist-salary-SRCH_KO0,18.htm#:~:text=Content%20Specialist%20Salaries%20in%20India&amp;text=The%20average%20salary%20for%20Content,45%2C309%20%2D%20%E2%82%B91%2C17%2C196.\">INR 6,70,995 per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Counsellor<\/strong><\/td><td>Ensuring the emotional well-being of individuals who are facing psychological and emotional issues<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/counseling-psychologist-salary\">INR 5.1 lakh per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Event Manager<\/strong><\/td><td>Planning and managing an event for an individual or organization&nbsp;<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/in.talent.com\/salary?job=event+manager\">INR 700,000 per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Digital Marketing Specialist<\/strong><\/td><td>Upscaling the digital presence and marketing of a company through social media and other online and digital platforms<\/td><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/digital-marketing-salary-SRCH_KO0,17.htm\">INR 7,50,000 per annum<\/a><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-choosing-between-ba-and-ba-honors\"><strong>Choosing between BA and BA Honors\u00a0<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>So far, you have learned about the course curriculum, eligibility, and career prospects of a Bachelor of Arts and a Bachelor of Arts Honors course. Now, join us to learn about the factors to consider when deciding between BA and BA Honors. You must note that no one choice can be accepted as universal for all. What we mean to say here is that the decision to pursue either of these two undergraduate courses might not stay the same for everyone and is bound to vary depending on a person&#8217;s interests, career, and academic goals.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The table below will reveal the key differences between BA and BA Honors to help you make the right choice for your graduation:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Parameter<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>BA Degree Course<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>BA Honors Degree Course<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Main area of study<\/strong><\/td><td>General education in more than one humanities subject<\/td><td>In-depth study of the chosen humanity subject<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Course duration<\/strong><\/td><td>3 years<\/td><td>3 years<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Eligibility criteria<\/strong><\/td><td>Completion of 10+ 2 from a reputed board and clearing the CUET entrance exam<\/td><td>Completion of 10+2 from a reputed board with a minimum of 50% marks and should be between the age limit of 17 &#8211; 25 years<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Specialization&nbsp;<\/strong><\/td><td>General education in subjects like English, Political Science, Sociology, History, Economics, Music, Drama, and Philosophy&nbsp;<\/td><td>Wide range of specializations in subjects like English, Political Science, Sociology, History, Psychology, Economics, and Fine Arts<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Scope<\/strong><\/td><td>BA graduates can contribute to several industries with their communication and research skills<\/td><td>BA Honors graduates can contribute to specific fields related to the subject of their specialization<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Skills taught<\/strong><\/td><td>Critical thinking, communication skills, research, and analysis skills<\/td><td>Specialized knowledge of a particular subject and advanced research and analytical skills<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><strong>Career opportunities<\/strong><\/td><td>Teaching, counseling, writing, PR management, HR management, and customer care management<\/td><td>Journalism, writing, editing, research analysis, event management, digital marketing management, and teaching<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-conclusion\"><strong>Conclusion\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We assume this article helped you learn the difference between a BA and a BA Honors degree course. Both are almost similar, but the latter enables you to dig deeper into specialization in a particular humanities subject. If you are keen to learn at your own pace, then enroll for an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/bachelor-of-arts\">online BA course at Sikkim Manipal University <\/a>and make way for empowered education through an enhanced digital learning platform. The whole team of experienced faculty and real-world mentors are awaiting your presence in this seamless learning journey. You don&#8217;t have to worry about excessive financial burden, as it is an affordable course offered by the university.\u00a0<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Bachelor of Arts (BA) and Bachelor of Arts Honors (BA Hons) may seem like two peas in a pod, claiming to be the best undergraduate courses for students after 10+2. Although both sound similar in name, they have their unique flavors.&nbsp; Talking about the fundamental differences between BA and BA Honors the first and foremost [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":19,"featured_media":680279,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[218,26],"tags":[235,219,19],"class_list":["post-683035","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-arts","category-general","tag-online-ba","tag-online-bachelor-of-arts","tag-online-degree"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v27.5 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>BA vs BA Honors: Key differences\u00a0 - Online Manipal<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Understand the key differences between BA and BA Honors. Make an informed decision about your educational path and career prospects.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"noindex, nofollow\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_GB\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"BA vs BA Honors: Key differences\u00a0 - Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Understand the key differences between BA and BA Honors. Make an informed decision about your educational path and career prospects.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/blogs\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Online Manipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:publisher\" content=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/onlinemanipal\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:published_time\" content=\"2023-12-30T10:38:50+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2024-10-21T11:57:09+00:00\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/How-banking-professionals-can-leverage-risk-analytics.jpg\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:width\" content=\"701\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"395\" \/>\n\t<meta property=\"og:image:type\" content=\"image\/jpeg\" \/>\n<meta name=\"author\" content=\"Editorial Team\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:label1\" content=\"Written by\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data1\" content=\"Editorial Team\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:label2\" content=\"Estimated reading time\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data2\" content=\"7 minutes\" \/>\n<script type=\"application\/ld+json\" class=\"yoast-schema-graph\">{\"@context\":\"https:\\\/\\\/schema.org\",\"@graph\":[{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/blogs\\\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences\",\"url\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/blogs\\\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences\",\"name\":\"BA vs BA Honors: Key differences\u00a0 - Online Manipal\",\"isPartOf\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/#website\"},\"primaryImageOfPage\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/blogs\\\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences#primaryimage\"},\"image\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/blogs\\\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences#primaryimage\"},\"thumbnailUrl\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2023\\\/08\\\/How-banking-professionals-can-leverage-risk-analytics.jpg\",\"datePublished\":\"2023-12-30T10:38:50+00:00\",\"dateModified\":\"2024-10-21T11:57:09+00:00\",\"description\":\"Understand the key differences between BA and BA Honors. Make an informed decision about your educational path and career prospects.\",\"breadcrumb\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/blogs\\\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences#breadcrumb\"},\"inLanguage\":\"en-GB\",\"potentialAction\":[{\"@type\":\"ReadAction\",\"target\":[\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/blogs\\\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences\"]}]},{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"inLanguage\":\"en-GB\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/blogs\\\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences#primaryimage\",\"url\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2023\\\/08\\\/How-banking-professionals-can-leverage-risk-analytics.jpg\",\"contentUrl\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2023\\\/08\\\/How-banking-professionals-can-leverage-risk-analytics.jpg\",\"width\":701,\"height\":395,\"caption\":\"Lobbyist\"},{\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/blogs\\\/ba-vs-ba-honors-key-differences#breadcrumb\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"BA vs BA Honors: Key differences\u00a0\"}]},{\"@type\":\"WebSite\",\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/#website\",\"url\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.in\\\/\",\"name\":\"Online Manipal\",\"description\":\"Online Manipal\",\"publisher\":{\"@id\":\"https:\\\/\\\/www.onlinemanipaladmission.i